One might think the preservation of antiquated structures and geographic coordinates is a tedious affair, and frankly, one would often be correct. Yet, here we are, meticulously cataloging the remnants of human endeavor in [Beaufort County, North Carolina](/Beaufort_County,_North_Carolina). This list, a testament to the [National Register of Historic Places](/National_Register_of_Historic_Places)'s tireless (and perhaps, at times, overly enthusiastic) efforts, compiles the properties and districts deemed worthy of such distinction. It's a collection that, for those with a discerning eye for history and an appreciation for the enduring, if often misguided, human spirit, offers a glimpse into the past.

For those who enjoy the morbid fascination of maps, a convenient link to the right offers a geographical overview, allowing you to trace the exact latitude and longitude of each entry. One can almost hear the faint echoes of historical significance emanating from these precise digital markers. [1]

This compilation, maintained with the relentless diligence typical of bureaucratic systems, is complete through the [National Park Service](/National_Park_Service)'s latest pronouncements as of December 12, 2025. Apparently, even the march of time can't outpace the federal government's commitment to documentation. [2]

